   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Fifty-six INSEPARABLE LOVE Scripture: Rom 8:35-39 Love is essential to human living Man as an emotional being needs love, and depends upon love.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Without love, human living is desolate; with love, life is wonderful.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Love meets man s need for warmth Human emotion needs warmth; only love has this warmth.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>With love, life is warm; without love, life is forlorn.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Love generates the warmest feelings in man.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The love of man Man s love is limited and lacking; therefore, it cannot satisfy the need of his emotion.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Give some practical illustrations.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Man s love will change and cease; therefore, it is not dependable.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Illustrate this point also.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The love of God Because God s love is unlimited and complete, it can satisfy man s emotions.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>God s love is unchanging, unceasing, and dependable.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Describe this through illustrations.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Since God s love is unchanging and unceasing, it is an inseparable love.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>No tribulation will cause His love to change or cease.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>How to partake of God s love God s love is given to us in Christ Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>God s love is manifested through the death of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>We must believe in Christ and His redemption in order to partake of God s love.</S>
   </TEXT>
